actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 101-352, by Ms. Slaughter (NY).

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 2939. The rule waives all points of order against the consideration of the conference report for failure to comply with the provisions of clause 2 of rule XXVIII and all points of order against the motions printed in the joint statement of the managers to dispose of Senate amendments Nos. 22, 23, 44, 69, 122, 201, 289 and 295 for failure to comply with the provisions of clause 7 of rule XVI.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 82.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by the Yeas and Nays: 362 - 45 (Roll no. 349).
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving certain points of order against consideration of the conference report (H.R. 2939) making appropriations for the foreign operations, export financing, and related programs for the fiscal year ending September 30, 1990, and for other purposes, and against certain amendments reported from conference in disagreement.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 2939 (foreign operations funding).
